<div class="c520_11">
<div id="v520.11.1"><span class="G3004 s">I say</span><span class="G3767 s"> then</span><span class="G683 s"> G3361, Hath</span><span class="G2316 s"> God</span><span class="G683 s"> cast away</span><span class="G846 s"> his</span><span class="G2992 s"> people</span><span class="G3361 s">? God forbid</span><span class="G1063 s"> G1096. For</span><span class="G1473 s"> I</span><span class="G2532 s"> also</span><span class="G1510 s"> am</span><span class="G2475 s"> an Israelite</span><span class="G1537 s">, of</span><span class="G4690 s"> the seed</span><span class="G11 s"> of Abraham</span><span class="G5443 s">, <i>of</i> the tribe</span><span class="G958 s"> of Benjamin</span>.</div>
<div id="v520.11.2"><span class="G2316 s">God</span><span class="G683 s"> hath</span><span class="G3756 s"> not</span><span class="G683 s"> cast away</span><span class="G846 s"> his</span><span class="G2992 s"> people</span><span class="G3739 s"> which</span><span class="G4267 s"> he foreknew</span><span class="G1492 s"> G2228. Wot ye</span><span class="G3756 s"> not</span><span class="G5101 s"> what</span><span class="G1124 s"> the scripture</span><span class="G3004 s"> saith</span><span class="G1722 s"> of</span><span class="G2243 s"> Elias</span><span class="G5613 s">? how</span><span class="G1793 s"> he maketh intercession</span><span class="G2316 s"> to God</span><span class="G2596 s"> against</span><span class="G2474 s"> Israel</span><span class="G3004 s">, saying</span>, <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (of Elias: Gr. in Elias?)</span></div>
<div id="v520.11.3"><span class="G2962 s">Lord</span><span class="G615 s">, they have killed</span><span class="G4675 s"> thy</span><span class="G4396 s"> prophets</span><span class="G2532 s">, and</span><span class="G2679 s"> digged down</span><span class="G4675 s"> thine</span><span class="G2379 s"> altars</span><span class="G2504 s">; and I</span><span class="G5275 s"> am left</span><span class="G3441 s"> alone</span><span class="G2532 s">, and</span><span class="G2212 s"> they seek</span><span class="G3450 s"> my</span><span class="G5590 s"> life</span>.</div>
<div id="v520.11.4"><span class="G235 s">But</span><span class="G5101 s"> what</span><span class="G3004 s"> saith</span><span class="G5538 s"> the answer of God</span><span class="G846 s"> unto him</span><span class="G2641 s">? I have reserved</span><span class="G1683 s"> to myself</span><span class="G2035 s"> seven thousand</span><span class="G435 s"> men</span><span class="G3748 s">, who</span><span class="G2578 s"> have</span><span class="G3756 s"> not</span><span class="G2578 s"> bowed</span><span class="G1119 s"> the knee</span><span class="G896 s"> to <i>the image of</i> Baal</span>.</div>
<div id="v520.11.5"><span class="G3779 s">Even so</span><span class="G3767 s"> then</span><span class="G1722 s"> at</span><span class="G3568 s"> this present</span><span class="G2540 s"> time</span><span class="G2532 s"> also</span><span class="G1096 s"> there is</span><span class="G3005 s"> a remnant</span><span class="G2596 s"> according</span><span class="G1589 s"> to the election</span><span class="G5485 s"> of grace</span>.</div>
<div id="v520.11.6"><span class="G1161 s">And</span><span class="G1487 s"> if</span><span class="G5485 s"> by grace</span><span class="G2089 s">, then <i>is it</i> no more</span><span class="G1537 s"> G3765 of</span><span class="G2041 s"> works</span><span class="G1893 s">: otherwise</span><span class="G5485 s"> grace</span><span class="G1096 s"> is</span><span class="G2089 s"> no more</span><span class="G5485 s"> G3765 grace</span><span class="G1161 s">. But</span><span class="G1487 s"> if</span><span class="G1537 s"> <i>it be</i> of</span><span class="G2041 s"> works</span><span class="G2076 s">, then is it</span><span class="G2089 s"> no more</span><span class="G5485 s"> G3765 grace</span><span class="G1893 s">: otherwise</span><span class="G2041 s"> work</span><span class="G2076 s"> is</span><span class="G2089 s"> no more</span><span class="G2041 s"> G3765 work</span>.</div>
<div id="v520.11.7"><span class="G5101 s">What</span><span class="G3767 s"> then</span><span class="G2474 s">? Israel</span><span class="G2013 s"> hath</span><span class="G3756 s"> not</span><span class="G2013 s"> obtained</span><span class="G5127 s"> that</span><span class="G3739 s"> which</span><span class="G1934 s"> he seeketh for</span><span class="G1161 s">; but</span><span class="G1589 s"> the election</span><span class="G2013 s"> hath obtained it</span><span class="G1161 s">, and</span><span class="G3062 s"> the rest</span><span class="G4456 s"> were blinded</span> <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (blinded: or, hardened)</span></div>
<div id="v520.11.8"><span class="G2531 s">(According as</span><span class="G1125 s"> it is written</span><span class="G2316 s">, God</span><span class="G1325 s"> hath given</span><span class="G846 s"> them</span><span class="G4151 s"> the spirit</span><span class="G2659 s"> of slumber</span><span class="G3788 s">, eyes</span><span class="G991 s"> that they should</span><span class="G3361 s"> not</span><span class="G991 s"> see</span><span class="G2532 s">, and</span><span class="G3775 s"> ears</span><span class="G191 s"> that they should</span><span class="G3361 s"> not</span><span class="G191 s"> hear</span><span class="G2193 s">;) unto</span><span class="G4594 s"> this</span><span class="G2250 s"> day</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (slumber: or, remorse)</span></div>
<div id="v520.11.9"><span class="G2532 s">And</span><span class="G1138 s"> David</span><span class="G3004 s"> saith</span><span class="G1096 s">, Let</span><span class="G846 s"> their</span><span class="G5132 s"> table</span><span class="G1096 s"> be made</span><span class="G1519 s"> a snare</span><span class="G2532 s"> G3803, and</span><span class="G1519 s"> a trap</span><span class="G2532 s"> G2339, and</span><span class="G1519 s"> a stumblingblock</span><span class="G2532 s"> G4625, and</span><span class="G1519 s"> a recompence</span><span class="G846 s"> G468 unto them</span>:</div>
<div id="v520.11.10"><span class="G4654 s">Let</span><span class="G846 s"> their</span><span class="G3788 s"> eyes</span><span class="G4654 s"> be darkened</span><span class="G991 s">, that they may</span><span class="G3361 s"> not</span><span class="G991 s"> see</span><span class="G2532 s">, and</span><span class="G4781 s"> bow down</span><span class="G846 s"> their</span><span class="G3577 s"> back</span><span class="G1275 s"> alway</span>.</div>
<div id="v520.11.11"><span class="G3004 s">I say</span><span class="G3767 s"> then</span><span class="G4417 s"> G3361, Have they stumbled</span><span class="G2443 s"> that</span><span class="G4098 s"> they should fall</span><span class="G3361 s">? God forbid</span><span class="G235 s"> G1096: but</span><span class="G846 s"> <i>rather</i> through their</span><span class="G3900 s"> fall</span><span class="G4991 s"> salvation</span><span class="G1484 s"> <i>is come</i> unto the Gentiles</span><span class="G1519 s">, for to</span><span class="G3863 s"> provoke</span><span class="G846 s"> them</span><span class="G3863 s"> to jealousy</span>.</div>
<div id="v520.11.12"><span class="G1161 s">Now</span><span class="G1487 s"> if</span><span class="G3900 s"> the fall</span><span class="G846 s"> of them</span><span class="G4149 s"> <i>be</i> the riches</span><span class="G2889 s"> of the world</span><span class="G2532 s">, and</span><span class="G2275 s"> the diminishing</span><span class="G846 s"> of them</span><span class="G4149 s"> the riches</span><span class="G1484 s"> of the Gentiles</span><span class="G4214 s">; how</span><span class="G3123 s"> much more</span><span class="G846 s"> their</span><span class="G4138 s"> fulness</span>? <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (diminishing: or, decay, or, loss)</span></div>
<div id="v520.11.13"><span class="G1063 s">For</span><span class="G3004 s"> I speak</span><span class="G5213 s"> to you</span><span class="G1484 s"> Gentiles</span><span class="G1909 s">, inasmuch as</span><span class="G1473 s"> G3745 G3303 I</span><span class="G1510 s"> am</span><span class="G652 s"> the apostle</span><span class="G1484 s"> of the Gentiles</span><span class="G1392 s">, I magnify</span><span class="G3450 s"> mine</span><span class="G1248 s"> office</span>:</div>
<div id="v520.11.14"><span class="G1513 s">If by any means</span><span class="G3863 s"> G4458 I may provoke to emulation</span><span class="G3450 s"> <i>them which are</i> my</span><span class="G4561 s"> flesh</span><span class="G2532 s">, and</span><span class="G4982 s"> might save</span><span class="G5100 s"> some</span><span class="G1537 s"> of</span><span class="G846 s"> them</span>.</div>
<div id="v520.11.15"><span class="G1063 s">For</span><span class="G1487 s"> if</span><span class="G580 s"> the casting away</span><span class="G846 s"> of them</span><span class="G2643 s"> <i>be</i> the reconciling</span><span class="G2889 s"> of the world</span><span class="G5101 s">, what</span><span class="G4356 s"> <i>shall</i> the receiving</span><span class="G1508 s"> <i>of them be</i>, but</span><span class="G2222 s"> life</span><span class="G1537 s"> from</span><span class="G3498 s"> the dead</span>?</div>
<div id="v520.11.16"><span class="G1161 s">For</span><span class="G1487 s"> if</span><span class="G536 s"> the firstfruit</span><span class="G40 s"> <i>be</i> holy</span><span class="G5445 s">, the lump</span><span class="G2532 s"> <i>is</i> also</span><span class="G2532 s"> <i>holy</i>: and</span><span class="G1487 s"> if</span><span class="G4491 s"> the root</span><span class="G40 s"> <i>be</i> holy</span><span class="G2532 s">, so</span><span class="G2798 s"> <i>are</i> the branches</span>.</div>
<div id="v520.11.17"><span class="G1161 s">And</span><span class="G1536 s"> if some</span><span class="G2798 s"> of the branches</span><span class="G1575 s"> be broken off</span><span class="G1161 s">, and</span><span class="G4771 s"> thou</span><span class="G5607 s">, being</span><span class="G65 s"> a wild olive tree</span><span class="G1461 s">, wert graffed in</span><span class="G1722 s"> among</span><span class="G846 s"> them</span><span class="G2532 s">, and</span><span class="G4791 s"> with</span><span class="G1096 s"> them</span><span class="G4791 s"> partakest</span><span class="G4491 s"> of the root</span><span class="G2532 s"> and</span><span class="G4096 s"> fatness</span><span class="G1636 s"> of the olive tree</span>; <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (among them: or, for them)</span></div>
<div id="v520.11.18"><span class="G2620 s">Boast</span><span class="G3361 s"> not</span><span class="G2620 s"> against</span><span class="G2798 s"> the branches</span><span class="G1161 s">. But</span><span class="G1487 s"> if</span><span class="G2620 s"> thou boast</span><span class="G4771 s">, thou</span><span class="G941 s"> bearest</span><span class="G3756 s"> not</span><span class="G4491 s"> the root</span><span class="G235 s">, but</span><span class="G4491 s"> the root</span><span class="G4571 s"> thee</span>.</div>
<div id="v520.11.19"><span class="G2046 s">Thou wilt say</span><span class="G3767 s"> then</span><span class="G2798 s">, The branches</span><span class="G1575 s"> were broken off</span><span class="G2443 s">, that</span><span class="G1473 s"> I</span><span class="G1461 s"> might be graffed in</span>.</div>
<div id="v520.11.20"><span class="G2573 s">Well</span><span class="G570 s">; because of unbelief</span><span class="G1575 s"> they were broken off</span><span class="G1161 s">, and</span><span class="G4771 s"> thou</span><span class="G2476 s"> standest</span><span class="G4102 s"> by faith</span><span class="G5309 s">. Be</span><span class="G3361 s"> not</span><span class="G5309 s"> highminded</span><span class="G235 s">, but</span><span class="G5399 s"> fear</span>:</div>
<div id="v520.11.21"><span class="G1063 s">For</span><span class="G1487 s"> if</span><span class="G2316 s"> God</span><span class="G5339 s"> spared</span><span class="G3756 s"> not</span><span class="G5449 s"> the natural</span><span class="G2798 s"> branches</span><span class="G4458 s"> G2596, <i>take heed</i> lest</span><span class="G5339 s"> G3381 he</span><span class="G3381 s"> also</span><span class="G5339 s"> spare</span><span class="G3761 s"> not</span><span class="G4675 s"> thee</span>.</div>
<div id="v520.11.22"><span class="G1492 s">Behold</span><span class="G3767 s"> therefore</span><span class="G5544 s"> the goodness</span><span class="G2532 s"> and</span><span class="G663 s"> severity</span><span class="G2316 s"> of God</span><span class="G1909 s">: on</span><span class="G4098 s"> them which fell</span><span class="G663 s"> G3303, severity</span><span class="G1161 s">; but</span><span class="G1909 s"> toward</span><span class="G4571 s"> thee</span><span class="G5544 s">, goodness</span><span class="G1437 s">, if</span><span class="G1961 s"> thou continue</span><span class="G5544 s"> in <i>his</i> goodness</span><span class="G1893 s">: otherwise</span><span class="G4771 s"> thou</span><span class="G2532 s"> also</span><span class="G1581 s"> shalt be cut off</span>.</div>
<div id="v520.11.23"><span class="G1161 s">And</span><span class="G1565 s"> they</span><span class="G2532 s"> also</span><span class="G3362 s">, if</span><span class="G1961 s"> they abide</span><span class="G3362 s"> not</span><span class="G570 s"> still in unbelief</span><span class="G1461 s">, shall be graffed in</span><span class="G1063 s">: for</span><span class="G2316 s"> God</span><span class="G2076 s"> is</span><span class="G1415 s"> able</span><span class="G1461 s"> to graff</span><span class="G846 s"> them</span><span class="G1461 s"> in</span><span class="G3825 s"> again</span>.</div>
<div id="v520.11.24"><span class="G1063 s">For</span><span class="G1487 s"> if</span><span class="G4771 s"> thou</span><span class="G1581 s"> wert cut</span><span class="G1537 s"> out of</span><span class="G65 s"> the olive tree which is wild</span><span class="G2596 s"> by</span><span class="G5449 s"> nature</span><span class="G2532 s">, and</span><span class="G1461 s"> wert graffed</span><span class="G3844 s"> contrary to</span><span class="G5449 s"> nature</span><span class="G1519 s"> into</span><span class="G2565 s"> a good olive tree</span><span class="G4214 s">: how much</span><span class="G3123 s"> more</span><span class="G3778 s"> shall these</span><span class="G2596 s">, which be the natural</span><span class="G1461 s"> G5449 <i>branches</i>, be graffed into</span><span class="G2398 s"> their own</span><span class="G1636 s"> olive tree</span>?</div>
<div id="v520.11.25"><span class="G1063 s">For</span><span class="G2309 s"> I would</span><span class="G3756 s"> not</span><span class="G80 s">, brethren</span><span class="G5209 s">, that ye</span><span class="G50 s"> should be ignorant</span><span class="G5124 s"> of this</span><span class="G3466 s"> mystery</span><span class="G3363 s">, lest</span><span class="G5600 s"> ye should be</span><span class="G5429 s"> wise</span><span class="G3844 s"> in</span><span class="G1438 s"> your own conceits</span><span class="G3754 s">; that</span><span class="G4457 s"> blindness</span><span class="G575 s"> in</span><span class="G3313 s"> part</span><span class="G1096 s"> is happened</span><span class="G2474 s"> to Israel</span><span class="G891 s">, until</span><span class="G4138 s"> G3739 the fulness</span><span class="G1484 s"> of the Gentiles</span><span class="G1525 s"> be come in</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (blindness: or, hardness)</span></div>
<div id="v520.11.26"><span class="G2532 s">And</span><span class="G3779 s"> so</span><span class="G3956 s"> all</span><span class="G2474 s"> Israel</span><span class="G4982 s"> shall be saved</span><span class="G2531 s">: as</span><span class="G1125 s"> it is written</span><span class="G2240 s">, There shall come</span><span class="G1537 s"> out of</span><span class="G4622 s"> Sion</span><span class="G4506 s"> the Deliverer</span><span class="G2532 s">, and</span><span class="G654 s"> shall turn away</span><span class="G763 s"> ungodliness</span><span class="G575 s"> from</span><span class="G2384 s"> Jacob</span>:</div>
<div id="v520.11.27"><span class="G2532 s">For</span><span class="G3778 s"> this</span><span class="G3844 s"> <i>is</i> my</span><span class="G1242 s"> G1700 covenant</span><span class="G846 s"> unto them</span><span class="G3752 s">, when</span><span class="G851 s"> I shall take away</span><span class="G846 s"> their</span><span class="G266 s"> sins</span>.</div>
<div id="v520.11.28"><span class="G2596 s">As concerning</span><span class="G2098 s"> G3303 the gospel</span><span class="G2190 s">, <i>they are</i> enemies</span><span class="G1223 s"> for your sakes</span><span class="G1161 s"> G5209: but</span><span class="G2596 s"> as touching</span><span class="G1589 s"> the election</span><span class="G27 s">, <i>they are</i> beloved</span><span class="G1223 s"> for</span><span class="G1223 s"> the fathers' G3962 sakes</span>.</div>
<div id="v520.11.29"><span class="G1063 s">For</span><span class="G5486 s"> the gifts</span><span class="G2532 s"> and</span><span class="G2821 s"> calling</span><span class="G2316 s"> of God</span><span class="G278 s"> <i>are</i> without repentance</span>.</div>
<div id="v520.11.30"><span class="G1063 s">For</span><span class="G5618 s"> as</span><span class="G5210 s"> G2532 ye</span><span class="G4218 s"> in times past</span><span class="G544 s"> have not believed</span><span class="G2316 s"> God</span><span class="G1161 s">, yet</span><span class="G1653 s"> have</span><span class="G3568 s"> now</span><span class="G1653 s"> obtained mercy</span><span class="G5130 s"> through</span><span class="G543 s"> their unbelief</span>: <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (believed: or, obeyed)</span></div>
<div id="v520.11.31"><span class="G3779 s">Even so</span><span class="G544 s"> have</span><span class="G3778 s"> these</span><span class="G2532 s"> also</span><span class="G3568 s"> now</span><span class="G544 s"> not believed</span><span class="G2443 s">, that</span><span class="G5212 s"> through your</span><span class="G1656 s"> mercy</span><span class="G846 s"> they</span><span class="G2532 s"> also</span><span class="G1653 s"> may obtain mercy</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (believed: or, obeyed)</span></div>
<div id="v520.11.32"><span class="G1063 s">For</span><span class="G2316 s"> God</span><span class="G4788 s"> hath concluded</span><span class="G3956 s"> them all</span><span class="G1519 s"> in</span><span class="G543 s"> unbelief</span><span class="G2443 s">, that</span><span class="G1653 s"> he might have mercy</span><span class="G3956 s"> upon all</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (concludedâ€¦: or, shut them all up together)</span></div>
<div id="v520.11.33"><span class="G5599 s">O</span><span class="G899 s"> the depth</span><span class="G4149 s"> of the riches</span><span class="G2532 s"> both</span><span class="G4678 s"> of the wisdom</span><span class="G2532 s"> and</span><span class="G1108 s"> knowledge</span><span class="G2316 s"> of God</span><span class="G5613 s">! how</span><span class="G419 s"> unsearchable</span><span class="G846 s"> <i>are</i> his</span><span class="G2917 s"> judgments</span><span class="G2532 s">, and</span><span class="G846 s"> his</span><span class="G3598 s"> ways</span><span class="G421 s"> past finding out</span>!</div>
<div id="v520.11.34"><span class="G1063 s">For</span><span class="G5101 s"> who</span><span class="G1097 s"> hath known</span><span class="G3563 s"> the mind</span><span class="G2962 s"> of the Lord</span><span class="G2228 s">? or</span><span class="G5101 s"> who</span><span class="G1096 s"> hath been</span><span class="G846 s"> his</span><span class="G4825 s"> counsellor</span>?</div>
<div id="v520.11.35"><span class="G2228 s">Or</span><span class="G5101 s"> who</span><span class="G4272 s"> hath first given</span><span class="G846 s"> to him</span><span class="G2532 s">, and</span><span class="G467 s"> it shall be recompensed</span><span class="G846 s"> unto him</span><span class="G467 s"> again</span>?</div>
<div id="v520.11.36"><span class="G3754 s">For</span><span class="G1537 s"> of</span><span class="G846 s"> him</span><span class="G2532 s">, and</span><span class="G1223 s"> through</span><span class="G846 s"> him</span><span class="G2532 s">, and</span><span class="G1519 s"> to</span><span class="G846 s"> him</span><span class="G3956 s">, <i>are</i> all things</span><span class="G846 s">: to whom</span><span class="G1391 s"> <i>be</i> glory</span><span class="G1519 s"> for</span><span class="G165 s"> ever</span><span class="G281 s">. Amen</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (whom: Gr. him)</span></div></div>
